begin_memory_text: The beginning of the conversation was a little frustrating because my partner's mic didn't function the way she needed it to, and I couldn't hear her. She was very tech-savvy, however, and was able to quickly resolve the problem. We started by talking about what we're planning to do today (what type of work).
middle_memory_text: During the middle of the conversation, we talked about places we have lived and what liked and didn't like about them (weather, culture, etc..) We talked about how the pandemic has affected our careers and plans for the near future. We discussed how possible relocation might be necessary, and where we might need to move to.
end_memory_text: Toward the end of the conversation, we talked about pets, My partner showed me her pets and I talked about how I would like to get one, but my living situation is too uncertain. My partner suggested fostering pets, and we talked about how that might be a good idea.
rest_of_day_open: Today is Tuesday. I have quite a bit of work to do, so I'm going to be very busy. I also need to run a couple of errands for my elderly parents. In the evenings, I'm planning to finish a collection of surface-pattern designs I've been working on as part of an online challenge.
critical_positive: The conversation flowed smoothly throughout most of the 25 minutes. Unlike most of my previous chats, we were not talking over one another, and that was nice. My partner was extremely intelligent and friendly, and I really enjoyed listening to her. She was also a good listener, and easy to talk to.
critical_negative: Unfortunately, I don't think my partner found me as interesting as I found her. Although she was extremely kind and personable, I felt much less intelligent than her, and sort of at a loss for what to talk about that she might find interesting. I found myself more than once doing the "nervous talk," where I was just saying anything that came to mind to compensate for my own discomfort. The conversation was much more pleasant when I let her do the talking.

begin_memory_text: I asked her what her day's plans were, and then she told me about her digital art business and how she wanted to get it off the ground. She told me she's going to do more gig-based stuff for money, since she's had a lot more time since the lockdown.
middle_memory_text: I told her about my jobs for the past year, specifically my Twitch streaming and the kinds of games I play. We talked about weather and natural disasters--wildfires in California, tornadoes in Oklahoma, and humidity vs dry heat in desert climates. She wants to move back to Nevada, where she lived when she was a kid.
end_memory_text: She talked more about Nevada and the state of Las Vegas in the early 70s versus today. I told her that my boyfriend and I might move out where she is, due to his job and the availability of positions in his field.
rest_of_day_open: I can definitely see it being busy. Today, for example, I have little time to do what I need to do, but as long as I set out to do significant tasks every day, I should be able to relax at the end of the week. I think, though it'll be busy, I'll have a good week. I may even complete one or two of my long-term goals this week, which is extremely exciting.
critical_positive: I think that each of us took the opportunity to talk more about ourselves more than we'd usually do so in other contexts. And I was definitely interested in what she had to say, because she's not a boring person. We each had an opinion about what the other had to say, so it seemed to flow pretty well with no silences.
critical_negative: I guess we didn't have a lot in common, so both of us had to make more of an effort to keep the conversation going. However, she's a good conversationalist and seemed to have good questions. We jumped around in subject, because it was difficult to find something to relate to what the other said.
